The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the White House to celebrate the progress made in the pro-life movement and to thank leaders and supporters for their dedication. Pence emphasized that the Trump administration has been committed to protecting the sanctity of human life and highlighted various actions taken, such as reinstating the Mexico City Policy, defunding Planned Parenthood, and appointing conservative judges, including three Supreme Court justices. He also discussed the administration's response to the COVID-19 pandemic and its focus on saving lives. Pence concluded by urging everyone to continue fighting for the cause of life and expressing his belief that the sanctity of life will be restored in American law.